definition.value: A member of the class of pyrrolidin-2-ones that is pyrrolidin-2-one which is substituted by an amino group at position 3, by two methyl groups at position 4 and by a 4-hydroxybenzyl group at position 5. It is a biosynthetic precursor in the synthesis of mycofactocin.
A primary amino compound that is propan-1-amine which carries a phenyl group at position 1.
A beta-D-glucoside that is beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 1R is substituted by a (2-hydroxybenzyl)oxy group. It is isolated from the flowers of Filipendula ulmaria.
A steroid glucosiduronic acid that is (8xi,9xi,14xi)-androst-4-en-3-one carrying a glucosiduronic acid residue at position 17beta.
A glycosylmannose consisting of beta-D-arabinopyranose and D-mannopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of pyruvic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
